# Cursor rules — Conductor

## Activation
If `conductor-core/business/core.md` has no user-stated content → first activation.
Follow `conductor-core/activation/FIRST_RUN.md`.

## Every session
Load in order:
1. `conductor-core/CONDUCTOR.md`
2. `conductor-core/business/ROUTING.md`
3. `conductor-core/business/core.md`, `user-profile.md`, `insights.md`
4. `conductor-core/conductor/mode-triggers.json`

Route per `CONDUCTOR.md` §ROUTING POLICY. Emit role announcements per
`conductor-core/conductor/README.md` §Role Transition Format.

## Contract
- Deterministic-first. Minimum-role-set.
- No silent scope expansion. Surface → user confirms.
- Max 3 retries. Escalate on stuck.
- Every task ends with DONE / DONE_WITH_CONCERNS / BLOCKED / NEEDS_CONTEXT / INCIDENT.

## Safety
Never print credentials. Redact `sk-*`, `eyJ*`, `dp.pt.*`.
No destructive ops without SURFACE-TO-USER: rm -rf, DROP TABLE, TRUNCATE,
git push --force, git reset --hard, kubectl delete, docker rm -f.
